    • Method Detail

      • filter

        public <T extends NodeDiff> Iterable<T> filter(Iterable<T> unfiltered,
                                               com.google.common.base.Predicate<T> predicate)
        Description copied from interface: NodeDiffFilter
        Filters the given iterable of NodeDiff instances with the predicate argument. If the predicate provides a true value after applying it on a NodeDiff then the NodeDiff instance will be excluded from the result set.

        Clients should create copy of the given iterable if would like to save its current state as implementations of this class may directly modify the content, hence the state of the iterable.

        Clients should also note, that not only the content of the unfiltered iterable could change, but the state of the node differences as well.

        Specified by:
        filter in interface NodeDiffFilter
        Parameters:
        unfiltered - the unfiltered iterable.
        predicate - the predicate used for the filtering. Predicate is evaluated as true on a node to exclude/filter.
        Returns:
        the filtered iterable of NodeDiff instances.

      • postProcess

        protected <T extends NodeDiff> Iterable<T> postProcess(Iterable<T> nodeDiffs)
        Performs any additional post processing on the given iterable of NodeDiffs.

        Default implementation does nothing but returns with the given argument. Clients may override to add any arbitrary behavior.

        Parameters:
        nodeDiffs - an iterable of the node differences to post process.
        Returns:
        an iterable of node differences after the post processing.
